Package cz.vse.java.services.clientSide

Class Client

  • java.lang.Object
    • cz.vse.java.services.serverSide.AService
      • cz.vse.java.services.clientSide.Client
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IService, IObserver, ISubject, java.lang.Runnable
    public class Client
extends AService
implements java.lang.Runnable, IObserver

    Class Client is Singleton by design pattern definition with only one possible instance of this class.

    The class has Thread-safe getInstance() creation mechanism implemented to be sure there is only one instance.

    This class is used for communicating with any other service, using a concept of MessageTask - delaying message sending to the moment of successful authentication message receiving.

    It also contains the only PreOrder it can contain.

    Written for project "Connections2".
    Version:
    05. 04. 2020 .vse.java.services
    Author:
    Vojtěch Pavlů
    See Also:
    Singleton at Wikipedia

      • send

        public boolean send​(IMessage message,
                    EServiceType type)

        Sends a message to the given service.

        Parameters:
        message - to be sent
        type - type of the service - the receiver.
        Returns:
        If the message was sent. The possibility of sending the message depends on what service is the receiver - when it's CLIENT, the sending will be refused. If it's router, it returns true. When it's any other service and is accessable, only then the message sending can be provided.
